<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Internal CSS Example</title>
  <!-- Internal CSS -->
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }
    header {
      background-color: #2e7d32;
      color: white;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    h1 {
      margin: 0;
    }
    h2 {
      color: #1565c0;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #1565c0;
      padding-bottom: 5px;
    }
    p {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #444;
      margin: 10px 20px;
    }
    ul {
      margin: 10px 40px;
      list-style-type: square;
      color: #333;
    }
    footer {
      background-color: #333;
      color: #fff;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 15px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Header -->
  <header>
    <h1>Welcome to My Webpage</h1>
    <p>Styled using Internal CSS</p>
  </header>

  <!-- Content -->
  <main>
    <h2>About Internal CSS</h2>
    <p>Internal CSS is written inside a <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> tag in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> section of an HTML document. It allows you to style multiple elements on the page without needing an external file.</p>

    <h2>Advantages</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Easy to apply styles to a single page</li>
      <li>No need for external CSS file</li>
      <li>Good for small projects or demos</li>
    </ul>
  </main>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2026 Internal CSS Demo</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
